children.text: There has not been adequate ventilation provided in this sub-floor, with the openings installed greater than 600mm from the corner, resulting in a damp environment, which according to the BCA, encourages timber rot, fungus growth and the potential for termite activity.
Part 3.4.1.2 of the National Construction Code’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) states that
‘Subfloor spaces must be provided with openings in external walls and internal subfloor walls in accordance with Table 3.4.1.1’,
‘a subfloor space must have openings placed not more than 600 mm in from corners’.
The builder will need to properly rectify the ventilation in accordance with part 3.4.1.2 of the BCA.
